k","start":235.94,"end":236.02},{"word":"and","start":236.02,"end":237.64},{"word":"bury","start":237.64,"end":238.6},{"word":"me","start":238.6,"end":240.62},{"word":"only","start":241.3,"end":242.02},{"word":"led","start":242.02,"end":242.3},{"word":"my","start":242.3,"end":243.6},{"word":"heart","start":243.6,"end":244.86},{"word":"to","start":244.86,"end":245.38},{"word":"you","start":245.38,"end":247.0},{"word":"I''ve","start":247.0,"end":248.26},{"word":"worn","start":248.26,"end":248.6},{"word":"the","start":248.6,"end":249.54},{"word":"blows","start":249.54,"end":249.54},{"word":"I''ve","start":250.22,"end":251.72},{"word":"felt","start":251.72,"end":252.02},{"word":"the","start":252.02,"end":252.96},{"word":"ache","start":252.96,"end":252.96},{"word":"but","start":253.26,"end":254.4},{"word":"I","start":254.4,"end":254.78},{"word":"stand","start":254.78,"end":255.32},{"word":"tall","start":255.32,"end":257.8},{"word":"By","start":258.28,"end":259.68},{"word":"mercy","start":259.68,"end":261.02},{"word":"and","start":261.02,"end":262.04},{"word":"grace","start":262.04,"end":262.42},{"word":"This","start":262.42,"end":263.74},{"word":"tower","start":263.74,"end":264.48},{"word":"of","start":264.48,"end":265.04},{"word":"scars","start":265.04,"end":266.36},{"word":"won''t","start":266.44,"end":273.0},{"word":"define","start":273.0,"end":274.2},{"word":"me","start":274.2,"end":275.26},{"word":"now","start":275.26,"end":275.3},{"word":"Thanks","start":293.1,"end":294.5},{"word":"for","start":294.5,"end":294.5},{"word":"watching","start":294.5,"end":294.5}],"lines":[{"text":"My road began in broken ground","start":0.0,"end":17.06},{"text":"in hurt and fear and fight","start":18.78,"end":21.0},{"text":"I used to stare into the dark and wonder who I''d be","start":26.22,"end":33.06},{"text":"in life","start":33.06,"end":34.4},{"text":"The years rolled by the weight stayed on","start":37.16,"end":43.82},{"text":"the battles cut down deep","start":45.02,"end":47.6},{"text":"Then I found the thief behind the pain","start":50.68,"end":55.52},{"text":"was after all in me","start":56.38,"end":61.48},{"text":"This tower of scars built through a lifetime of pain","start":63.56,"end":73.86},{"text":"Won''t be the thing that names me now there''s still fire in","start":74.46,"end":85.94},{"text":"these veins I''ve worn the blows I''ve felt the ache","start":85.94,"end":93.84},{"text":"but I''m still here","start":94.58,"end":98.16},{"text":"And I won''t break","start":100.5,"end":104.02},{"text":"I searched for peace in empty arms","start":109.32,"end":114.06},{"text":"in places love had failed","start":115.04,"end":117.56},{"text":"The losses stacked like prison walls","start":120.58,"end":125.44},{"text":"till hope itself looked frail","start":127.16,"end":130.28},{"text":"I looked left and right then down below stuck in the dust","start":131.56,"end":138.6},{"text":"I''d made","start":138.6,"end":140.12},{"text":"Then heaven met me in that pit","start":141.72,"end":145.28},{"text":"when I finally called your name This tower of scars built through","start":146.14,"end":159.54},{"text":"a lifetime of pain","start":159.54,"end":163.84},{"text":"Won''t be the thing that names me now there''s still fire in","start":164.36,"end":175.68},{"text":"these veins","start":175.68,"end":177.42},{"text":"I''ve worn the blows I''ve felt the ache","start":178.26,"end":183.74},{"text":"but I''m still here","start":184.68,"end":187.4},{"text":"And I won''t break These scars these wounds these tears these years","start":190.58,"end":196.84},{"text":"I laid them down I leave them here","start":196.84,"end":200.12},{"text":"Now every second every breath","start":204.08,"end":208.06},{"text":"every hour every day I trust the one who carried me and","start":208.4,"end":217.9},{"text":"lights my way","start":217.9,"end":221.84},{"text":"This tower of scars","start":222.84,"end":227.66},{"text":"stands as proof I made it through What tried to break and","start":227.98,"end":237.64},{"text":"bury me","start":237.64,"end":240.62},{"text":"only led my heart to you I''ve worn the blows","start":241.3,"end":249.54},{"text":"I''ve felt the ache but I stand tall","start":250.22,"end":257.8},{"text":"By mercy and grace This tower of scars won''t define me now","start":258.28,"end":275.3},{"text":"Thanks for watching","start":293.1,"end":294.5}],"duration":294.5,"plain_text":"My road began in broken ground, in hurt and fear and fight I used to stare into the dark and wonder who I''d be in life The years rolled by, the weight stayed on, the battles cut down deep Then I found the thief behind the pain, was after all in me This tower of scars, built through a lifetime of pain Won''t be the thing that names me now, there''s still fire in these veins I''ve worn the blows, I''ve felt the ache, but I''m still here And I won''t break I searched for peace in empty arms, in places love had failed The losses stacked like prison walls, till hope itself looked frail I looked left and right then down below, stuck in the dust I''d made Then heaven met me in that pit, when I finally called your name This tower of scars, built through a lifetime of pain Won''t be the thing that names me now, there''s still fire in these veins I''ve worn the blows, I''ve felt the ache, but I''m still here And I won''t break These scars, these wounds, these tears, these years I laid them down, I leave them here Now every second, every breath, every hour, every day I trust the one who carried me, and lights my way This tower of scars, stands as proof I made it through What tried to break and bury me, only led my heart to you I''ve worn the blows, I''ve felt the ache, but I stand tall By mercy and grace This tower of scars, won''t define me now Thanks for watching!"}', transcript_state = 'ready', updated_at = CURRENT_TIMESTAMP WHERE slug = 'tower-of-scars';

